    <item>
      <title>Re: Puller OOR?  No xp for group!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&amp;message.id=13190#M13190</link>
      <description>No, No, No, and No.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Speaking as someone who was invovled in the reason this code was&#xD;
implemented, and someone who did the quad kiting group bonus trick, and&#xD;
as someone who pulls for groups legit and experiences this bug, I will&#xD;
summarize this in its correct form.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
This thread has a lot of useful information and a lot of irrelevant&#xD;
information and the problem is people continue to merge and then&#xD;
attempt to break them apart to the point that someone who doesn't&#xD;
understand this issue is not going to be any closer to grasping it by&#xD;
the time they work through the pages of the thread. I'm sure that is&#xD;
part of the reason a year has passed with this thread, let alone 6&#xD;
years of the bug, without any resolution.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
A poster above wrote somewhat unintelligibly, but they nailed it on the&#xD;
head. The problem with this code was introduced to prevent mages,&#xD;
necros, and shamans from AFKing with their pets holding a camp, sitting&#xD;
somewhere far out of range and getting free exp all night. If the pet&#xD;
could clear the camp over and over and not die, you could return when&#xD;
you pleased with levels upon levels of free exp. This occured in 1999&#xD;
only a few months after the game went live.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
At the time of this code implementation pets were kos and had faction.&#xD;
If you cleared a camp and placed your pet there, when the mobs&#xD;
respawned the pets would get hit by the mobs and proceed to clear the&#xD;
camp for you. At this time if you were nearby you would be added to the&#xD;
hatelist, but if you were too far out of range, you would not generate&#xD;
any aggro at all. You would get free experience and in the event your&#xD;
pet died, you would just sit wherever you went without getting&#xD;
attacked, coming back bummed out that you left yourself in all night&#xD;
only to be out of food and drink.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Their first step in the solution was: If your pet is aggro to&#xD;
something, you are aggro to something. While the pet retains its own&#xD;
hate levels, you being the owner also suffer the consequences of your&#xD;
pet's actions. Now for the AFKer's, when your pet died trying to hold&#xD;
the camp, the mobs would come running for you. Also if a second mob&#xD;
spawned while your pet was fighting one and it hit your pet, you'd be&#xD;
added to the hate list and if you were sitting while afk, your sit&#xD;
aggro would be greater than the assist aggro your pet gained, and the&#xD;
add or second spawn would come running and kill you. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
The problem was there is still a max "persue" range, and so if you were&#xD;
a very far, very safe amount, you would still get experience and in&#xD;
either of these new events, you would still be safe. Your name would&#xD;
stay on the hatelist for a while (back then mobs had their own bluring&#xD;
autoblur, timed blur, and other events, so it wouldn't be perm), but it&#xD;
would definately keep you aggro for enough time that if you ran into&#xD;
"persue" range, they would come running for you.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
----&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
So folks are still safely getting experience from pets at this point.&#xD;
So instead of the smart solution (which is the most recent, pets have&#xD;
no faction and are not KOS), someone came up with the idea that if you&#xD;
were too far from where a mob was dying and you were on its hatelist,&#xD;
you would not get experience for the kill. This stopped all afk pet exp&#xD;
farmers from being able to gain any exp unless everyone on the hatelist&#xD;
and eligible for the pool of experience "to be applied" upon death were&#xD;
there near it.&amp;nbsp; The problem was, this was not tied to pets or people&#xD;
solo or anything, it was a universal change applied to hatelist and exp&#xD;
code across the board.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
This change has never been reversed, though the code that has reduced&#xD;
the range I'm willing to bet is additional. I'd even wager a modern dev&#xD;
looking at the legacy fix&amp;nbsp; wouldn't realize what they are seeing let&#xD;
alone that it&amp;nbsp; is the cause.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
***This is the sole reason that you lose exp due to being out of range.&#xD;
There is no such thing as "first aggro".&amp;nbsp; If you have a group of 6 and&#xD;
the puller brings the mob, have anyone else in the group get on the&#xD;
hatelist by casting a detrimental spell on the mob (damage or not,&#xD;
either way) and then run as far away as they can before the mob dies.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
It obviously has to meet the distance requirements but the point is it&#xD;
will not only happen to the puller, it happens to everyone on the&#xD;
hatelist that is eligible for experience. Meaning someone out of the&#xD;
group can run off and not affect your mob if they run off and your&#xD;
group stays put and finishes it.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
------&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
That's the issue and its what needs to be looked into.&amp;nbsp; As a summary&#xD;
about the issues other people are confusing, here is just a FYI on the&#xD;
"group bonus" code which _DOES_NOT_HAVE_ANYTHING_TO_DO_WITH_THE_ABOVE,&#xD;
so please take the following text as something totally unrelated.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
When the group experience bonuses were tuned during the Planes of Power&#xD;
expansion, there was a way to exploit this. You would group up with&#xD;
someone and then you would move to one side of the zone and they would&#xD;
move to the other.&amp;nbsp; You could add up to 6 people, and the more you&#xD;
added, the better the bonus got. Here was the problem, and I'll use&#xD;
Dreadlands as an example.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Before the group bonuses, exploit, and then nerf, if Player A was at&#xD;
the spires in dreadlands killing skeletons and Player B was at Karnor's&#xD;
Castle wall killing random trash, both players would receive solo&#xD;
experience because they were not in range of each other.&amp;nbsp; The devs came&#xD;
in and added bonuses for grouping to address a long-broken system and&#xD;
to make grouping more beneficial than soloing, trying to create a&#xD;
preference for grouping over soloing because it was more worthwhile.&#xD;
Sadly the soloers took advantage of this. Now with the new bonuses,&#xD;
Player A at the spires still got "solo" exp because of how far apart&#xD;
they were, but because of the fact Player A was grouped with Player B,&#xD;
Player A got the bonus for being grouped added as a modifier onto the&#xD;
experience. So instead of getting the great solo experience of before,&#xD;
they got even BETTER experience.&amp;nbsp; So you group 6 soloers, you all get&#xD;
out of range of each other, and you all get solo experience for a kill,&#xD;
modified by the bonus for being grouped with 6, and you were making&#xD;
insane amount of exp.&amp;nbsp; Folks quadding in Plane of Fire could get 2-3 aa&#xD;
per 4 mobs, and swarm kiting bards could make 75-100aa in a single&#xD;
pull.&amp;nbsp; You can imagine its not possible, but I did it and believe me it&#xD;
was.&amp;nbsp; If you had a bunch of soloing friends then you would all reap the&#xD;
benefits, but some of the most wretched of the bunch actually would&#xD;
group 5 bots afk at a zone line and then go off and solo just to&#xD;
powerlever themselves or with one other person next to them usually&#xD;
several levels under but enough to get exp and powerlevel the second&#xD;
person super fast.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
They fixed this bug by making the bonus check be based on how close you&#xD;
were to the rest of the members of your party, not based on the fact&#xD;
you were grouped. This change did not affect the original above bug in&#xD;
any way shape or form. It was merely added to the routine that decides&#xD;
whether or not "You gain party experience!" or "You gain experience!".&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
If its party experience, you get the bonus modifier, its its regular&#xD;
experience, you get regular experience.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
And that folks, is the bottom line.&amp;nbsp; If devs or QA or anyone still&#xD;
wishes to resolve the frustration of this bug, please reference the&#xD;
changes in 1999 to the HATELIST and exp for radius, not anything else&#xD;
or related to group bonuses.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Thank you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
