      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;By leaving this "no exp if out of range" code in, they also helped to deter the rampant KS'ing problem that was about in kunark era. Where a puller would go out and get a mob only to have it snagged, by druids(mostly in my exp) or other soloers, before the pull managed to get back to the group. Since most KS'ers wouldn't dare fight the mob within range of the group they KS'ed the pull from (for fear of blowing their mana pull in a burn fight) they would pull it away; being out of range when the mob was killed.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I believe this is why they have left it in for so long, because it has helped solve Kill Stealing problems. You can still loot the corpse, but most ks'ing was done for exp in outdoor zones.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
